<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7269> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7269" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Senator in 129. Being no. 15 in the list of members of the consilium in the SC de agro Pergameno of 129, he was probably above the lowest rank. If so, he may be Rubrius (1). Tr. Pl. 133?, rather than C.? Rubrius (2). Tr. Pl. 123 or 122. (LRT) His tribe is given as Poplilia in Copy A of the SC and Pupinia in Copy B (Sherk, RDGE no. 12), but note AEpig. 1941, 148-ILLRP 341: C. Rubrio C. f. Pop(lilia). On the dating to 129, see above, on M'. Aquillius (10).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6944> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6944" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Senator in 129 (S. C. de Agro Pergameno). Perhaps a colleague of C. Gracchus (see 122, Tribunes of the Plebs)." .
